  <context>
    <background>
      Per r1 ledger entry RB-T070-01 (filed 2026-05-31, fix-by 2026-07-31): same root-cause pattern as RB-T034-01 (`AgentConfigurationService`). The 3 public async methods accept `CancellationToken` and forward to `IDistributedCache` (MemoryDistributedCache in tests, Redis in production), neither of which raises `OperationCanceledException` synchronously on already-cancelled tokens for in-process / fast-path operations.

      No in-process caller passes a non-default token today; the unit tests assert the defensive cancellation pattern. The 1-line `ThrowIfCancellationRequested()` add per method closes the contract violation.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="029" status="must-be-complete">Phase 2 exit triple-run validation before Phase 3 starts</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

