    <step order="3">Add `cancellationToken.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();` as the FIRST statement of each of the 3 methods.</step>
    <step order="4">Build BFF: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Zero new warnings.</step>
    <step order="5">Edit `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Agent/AgentConversationServiceTests.cs`: remove `Skip = "..."` on the 3 RespectsCancellationToken tests; remove per-test `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` overrides.</step>
    <step order="6">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~AgentConversationServiceTests"`. All 3 re-enabled tests must pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Update ledger row RB-T070-01: status → `repaired`, fix-commit SHA placeholder + today's date.</step>
    <step order="8">Commit: `fix(bff-api): honor CancellationToken in AgentConversationService 3 methods (RB-T070-01; repaired)` per NFR-04.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/current-task.md` with completion + commit SHA.</step>
